   - `funext x` is used to extend the equality to all points in space-time, as the functions are equal if they are equal at every point.
   - The `simp_all` tactic is applied with lemmas about the Lorentz group action (`LorentzGroup.action_ofVecMul`, etc.) to show that the transformed derivatives match.
   - Finally, `rfl` confirms that the simplified expressions are definitionally equal.

This proof leverages the linearity of the derivative and the compatibility of the Lorentz group action with the derivative operator in Minkowski space, ensuring that the transformation of the derivative is the same as taking the derivative of the transformed field.
